    "The hidden influence criterion may also be attractive because it lays a connection to the burgeoning debate about AI deception.",
    "However, it is crucial to recognise that manipulation and deception are not the same thing see Cohen (2023) for a recent assessment.",
    "Hidden influence may not even provide a necessary criterion for manipulation, as many researchers have pointed out, see Klenk (2021c).",
    "Thanks to an anonymous referee for suggesting this helpful example.",
    "This is explained, for example, by the failure of the bypassing rationality criterion."
